NGINX DOCKER CONTAINER:

-- docker pull imagename:tag
-- docker run -d --name container_name  imagename:tag  ( -d detach mode)

=====================================================================================

COPY FILES TO DOCKER CONTAINER:

docker cp <local_path> <container_name_or_id>:<container_path>

eg: docker cp /tmp/index.html webserver:/var/www/html/

======================================================================================

RE-TAG & RE-NAME DOCKER IMAGE :

docker tag image:tag new_image_name:new_tag_name

======================================================================================

CREATE DOCKER IMAGE FROM CONTAINER:

docker commit <container_name_or_id> <new_image_name>:<tag>
Example: docker commit ubuntu_latest news:xfusion

This is useful when youâ€™ve made manual changes inside a running container 
(installed packages, changed files, etc.) and want to save those changes as a new image.

========================================================================================
